DORA Framework / Accelerate Metrics: 
--------------------------------------
How fequently we are able to Push to Production


Mean Time to resolve: MTTR - Operation Metrics for DevOPs/SRE Team
How quickly can we resolve the incidents on Production

If I dont play Soccer, It doesnt matter if Half of England is celebrating
Development Team may not bother about OPs Metrics.

Installed Version Index


UI and UX Version of Ketchup bottle

Build & Integration Frequency

Production Incident Count



Time to Pivot: Innovation Metrics -- How soon can we accomodate the change in the Market Conditions.
Ex: GST got introduced, How soon can banking System adapt these new changes.
Ex2: Covid --- Remote working -- How soon can u adapt to cahnges in operations. Ranging from 4 days to 45 days


Introduction to the metrics depends on the Teams maturity

Leakage ---------- Engineer + OPs Team together -- Only then We can have a robust fix.
OPs Team can only throw the water in glass and put it back under the leaking tap.

Release Stabilization Period -- No regression
Ex: MS Excel. Old features matter more than new Features

Lead Time for Changes
Business ask ----------> time to build ( 1/2/3// Sprints)
Prioritization of what matters most.

Customer Cycle Time

Time - to - Learn: - new technologies - Cloud, AI/ML, Dosckerization


Employee Satisfaction:

------------------------------

Which Metrics to use depends on the Context

Find out In whch quadrant does our Product fall? - Is it new? Is it Live?

new Product: MVP focused. Innovation focused. New era Technology.
Standardization -> Automation

Also depends on How long are we supporting this version.

4 quadrant Product Stage Approach by Gartner

Is your Product Innovative categroy -- Block Chain... etc
They dont have any basline. They are Pioneers.
What matters is --- Get Customer feedback and adapt 
Step 1 - Development

Step 2 - Scale. Also work on Ops. Need Good Dev OPs Collaboration

If Stable Products, Work is mostly on small config changes



